\pard\pardeftab720\sa298\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs36 \cf0 \strokec2 What the Pro Sees in Their Dashboard\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs24 \cf0 Every pro has a "My Network" section in their dashboard that shows:\
\'95Their referral link (copy button)\
\'95Their QR code (download button)\
\'95Number of pros they have personally referred\
\'95Total active pros in their downline (all levels)\
\'95Network income earned this month (broken out by level)\
\'95Network income earned all-time\
\'95A simple tree view showing who they referred and who those people referred\
This transparency is intentional. The more a pro can see their network growing and their income compounding, the more motivated they are to keep recruiting.\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \strokec0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa298\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs36 \cf0 \strokec2 Fraud Prevention\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs24 \cf0 Three rules prevent gaming the system:\
Rule 1 \'97 Self-referral is blocked. A pro cannot use their own referral link to create a second account. The system checks email, phone number, and business address against existing records.\
Rule 2 \'97 Circular referrals are blocked. The system checks that no referral chain creates a loop (A refers B, B refers A). If detected, the second referral is rejected and flagged for admin review.\
Rule 3 \'97 Jobs must be verified before commission is paid. Network income is only calculated on jobs where the homeowner has confirmed completion (either via the TrustyPro app or via a confirmation code sent to the homeowner's phone). Unconfirmed jobs do not generate network income.\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \strokec0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa298\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs36 \cf0 \strokec2 Tracking for Charter Partners Specifically\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs24 \cf0 Because Charter Partners are the top of the tree, their tracking has one additional layer: the Charter Partner Dashboard shows them a full multi-level view of their entire downline \'97 not just the people they personally referred, but all L2, L3, and L4 pros beneath them, along with each person's job activity and the income generated at each level.\
This is the single most powerful retention tool for Charter Partners. When a Charter Partner can watch their network grow in real time and see the income compounding, they become the platform's most effective recruiters.\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \strokec0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa298\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs36 \cf0 \strokec2 Physical Materials Workflow \'97 Step by Step\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs24 \cf0 1.Pro submits application 
\f3 \uc0\u8594 
\f1  system stores business mailing address\
2.Pro signs agreement electronically 
\f3 \uc0\u8594 
\f1  agreement stored in DB with timestamp\
3.Pro's subscription payment clears 
\f3 \uc0\u8594 
\f1  status changes from pending to active\
4.Activation event fires 
\f3 \uc0\u8594 
\f1  print job API call triggered automatically\
5.Print vendor produces materials with pro's name, trade, and unique QR code\
6.Kit ships to business address 
\f3 \uc0\u8594 
\f1  tracking number stored in DB\
7.Pro receives kit within 5 business days\
8.Pro can reorder additional materials from their dashboard at cost ($12\'9618/kit)\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \strokec0 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa298\partightenfactor0

